                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d209">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">824.6354/127</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Chief of the Division of Latin American
                        Affairs</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Duggan</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-12-07">December 7,
                            1936</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>During a conversation this morning with the Bolivian Minister, I inquired whether
                    he had ever received instructions to consult with the Department regarding
                    cooperation between the two countries in matters pertaining to tin. The Minister
                    replied that when the Minister of Finance passed through this country several
                    months ago, the latter said that he would send instructions shortly after his
                    return to La Paz. The Minister said he would write the Minister of Finance
                    reminding him of this conversation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Laurence Duggan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
